23:["$","h2","28",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"When to Choose Which—Based on Real 2026 Use Cases"}]
24:["$","p","30",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["• Choose No-Code if: You're launching a sales enablement portal in <72 hours, need GDPR-compliant forms with Zapier sync, or empowering regional teams to self-serve dashboards."]}]
25:["$","p","32",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["• Choose Low-Code if: You're extending SAP S/4HANA with a custom field service module, building HIPAA-compliant patient intake, or require SOC 2 audit trails and granular RBAC."]}]
26:["$","h2","34",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"FAQ: Your Top Questions—Answered with 2026 Data"}]
27:["$","h3","36",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Q1: Can no-code apps scale to enterprise workloads?"}]
28:["$","p","37",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Yes—but only with platform-native scaling (e.g., Bubble's new Cloudflare Workers integration or Softr's AWS-backed plans). Still, >92% of enterprises exceeding 200K monthly active users migrate critical apps to low-code within 18 months (Forrester, 2025)."]}]
29:["$","h3","39",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Q2: Do low-code platforms eliminate the need for developers?"}]
2a:["$","p","40",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: No—they shift developer roles from writing boilerplate to designing architecture, securing integrations, and governing reuse. Teams using low-code see 40% faster feature delivery—but still require at least one full-stack engineer per 5 citizen developers."]}]
2b:["$","h3","42",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Q3: Is vendor lock-in worse with no-code?"}]
2c:["$","p","43",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Historically yes—but 2026's top no-code tools now offer data portability (SQL exports, RESTful APIs) and modular design. Lock-in risk is now ~35% lower than in 2022 (G2 Enterprise Stack Survey)."]}]
2d:["$","h3","45",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Q4: Are AI-assisted builders blurring the line?"}]
2e:["$","p","46",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Partially. AI copilots (e.g., Retool AI, Bubble AI) help generate logic or debug flows—but they don't replace architectural decisions. The line remains sharp: no-code = no code *written*, low-code = code *augmented*."]}]
2f:["$","h2","48",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#e8e0f7] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Final Recommendation: Start No-Code, Scale Smart"}]
30:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-[#c4b5fd] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["In 2026, the winning strategy isn't choosing one over the other—it's adopting a *tiered stack*. Launch customer feedback portals, HR onboarding flows, or internal wikis with no-code. Then use low-code for mission-critical systems requiring compliance, performance, or deep legacy integration. Audit your toolchain quarterly: 68% of high-performing teams rotate or augment platforms annually (nocode-tools.net 2026 Platform Maturity Report). Prioritize interoperability, not ideology—and always measure ROI in time-to-value, not lines of code."]}]
